11/08/2004
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Police chiefs from four countries in Southeast Europe -- Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro -- discussed regional security issues together with UNMIK during a meeting in Podgorica Tuesday (10 August). 
They agreed that Olympics-related security is a special challenge and priority for all police structures in the region. 
(Tanjug, B92, Makfax, NTV Hayat - 10/08/04)
